A cyberpunk cityscape of Singapore at night, featuring towering skyscrapers with glowing neon advertisements reflected in rain-slicked streets. In the foreground, translucent holographic barriers shimmer faintly between buildings, barely visible like ghostly curtains. Citizens walk freely through these phantom walls, unaware or unbothered, their silhouettes casting long shadows. Above the city, an enormous all-seeing eye made of digital pixels floats in the smoggy sky, its gaze diffused and unfocused. The architecture blends traditional Singaporean shophouses with sleek chrome towers, fiber optic cables running like veins through the urban landscape. The color palette emphasizes deep magentas, electric blues, and sickly greens, with fog rolling through the streets creating an atmosphere of ambient surveillance that exists more in perception than reality.
